fore expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:153:    reachability-metadata-schema-vX.Y.Z.json\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:236:- **FR-CI-5** `verify-new-library-version-compatibility` caps each scheduled run at a fixed library budget and at most 30 newer versions per library, expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, and creates one aggregated GitHub issue per failed `(library, version)` pair.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:271:- Mirrored stats under `stats/` and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\nforge/utility_scripts/jacoco_parser.py:8:Parses lines coverage from JaCoCo XML and aggregates all <counter type='LINE'> elements.\nforge/utility_scripts/native_test_verification.py:739:        _print_aggregated_metadata_path(output_dir)\nforge/utility_scripts/native_test_verification.py:750:def _print_aggregated_metadata_path(output_dir: str) -> None:\nforge/utility_scripts/native_test_verification.py:751:    \"\"\"Print only the path to the merged reachability metadata file.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/large_library_progress.py:246:        \"\"\"Record aggregate dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/native_metadata_exploration.py:185:        merge_rc = _run_gradle(merge_cmd, reachability_repo_path, merge_log_path, step_timeout_seconds)\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
